## v1.1.0 (2026-06-25)

**Changed by:** Inference360 issue 257 engine/checkpoint comparison session.
**Verification:** verified-local

### What changed
- Expanded the skill from fresh-allocation staging validation to include issue 257 IFM 4B converted-checkpoint corruption debugging.
- Added a reproducible vLLM/SGLang/HF/native XLLM comparison workflow with seed 42, sentinel seed 0, logprobs, token IDs, raw request/response JSONL, launch-command capture, and Slurm cleanup evidence.
- Added failed-attempt rows for raw GitHub disclosure blocking, missing SGLang modules, SGLang parser incompatibility, converted-checkpoint remote-code import failure, and legacy model-name guard failures.
- Added observed issue 257 results and local validation evidence from PR 279 / commit f155b1f.

### Why
The previous version covered fresh H200 Slurm control allocation validation but did not preserve the issue-257-specific corruption investigation workflow. The new evidence showed deterministic vLLM corruption with useful logprob/token-ID details, while SGLang/HF/native XLLM comparison still needed a compatible original checkpoint/runtime on another cluster.

